description.narrative:
-Percentage of needs met with the upgrade of the dajpredlog website out of the total needs identified by the MLS;
-Number of procedures provided in electronic format, accessible to citizens from Gostivar municipality;
-Number of local governments that do  not have preconditions for advancing e-service delivery on local level (web site);
-"Programme for Financial Support to IMC for 2018" prepared (Y/N);
-Number of operational activities for IMC supported;
-Number of studies on ITP prepared;
-Action Plan for 2018 - 2020 prepared (Y/N);
-Number of Registers for Potentials for Rural Tourism developed;
-Number of technical documentations prepared for supporting rural tourism in preselected municipalities.

comment.narrative:
-Currently used web site www.dajpredlog.mk is limited to communication between MLS and citizens only. Currently for communication, MLS officials are using private email addresses. CSOs, municipalities, line ministries, neighborhood units are not included;
-0 procedures available in electronic format accessible to citizens;
-6 local governments do not have official websites;
-Urban local governments have one-stop-shops but no assessment on their functionality;
-Rural local governments do not have one-stop-shops and no assessment on how to deliver e-services;
-Last prepared "Programme for Financial Support to IMC" refers to 2016;
- 5 ongoing operational activities for IMC already supported in 2016;
- No conceptualization and pre-feasibility studies prepared for Interregional Technology Park;
- Representatives from Vardar and East planning regions attended two study visits in Technology and Innovation Parks in the Czech Republic;
- Last prepared Action Plan for implementation of the Local Government Sustainable Development Programme 2015 – 2020 is referring to the period 2015 – 2017;
- Registers for potentials for rural tourism available for 4 out of 8 planning regions;
- Technical documentation for rural tourism development in the least developed municipalities of 4 out of 8 regions;

1st Quarter 2016
•	Local Assistant for documentation and administrative procedures in the Municipality of Gostivar hired in February in the frameworks of the activity for establishing eRegulation System for administrative procedures
	Center for Development of Pelagonija Planning Region 
•	Integrated Network for Regional Development (INRD), developed and submitted two project applications, one to CIVICA MOBILITAS entitled Improving energy efficiency and using renewable energy sources and the second one to the Government entitled Lobbying in the decision-making process relating to regulations for urban planning;
•	Two meetings held with the regional chambers from Prilep, Bitola and Kicevo in the frameworks of the campaign for wider involvement of the regional stakeholders in the network activities;
•	Established business relations with the Republic of Turkey trough the chief promoter of the Republic of Macedonia for Izmir Region, Mr. Alev Sulaiman.


	Center for Development of Northeast Planning Region
•	Platform for Reginal Rural Action of the Northeast Planning Region implemented two training on topics of rural tourism development (“Business Ideas for Development of Rural Tourism” and “Organic Farming as a Potential for Rural Tourism”) with participation of 140 participants.

	Centre for Development of Vardar Planning Region purchased 4 mobile awnings intended to cover the stands while organizing commercial and tourist events in VPR; promotional event for the awnings was held.

	Signed second Annexes with the 3 CDPR (Pelagonia, Northeast and Vardar) for extension of the period of implementation of the activities and reallocation of incurred savings.
	All Web portals for investing (including e-data base) in the 5 planning regions have permanent IT addresses and are in function.

	Center for Development of the Southwest Planning Region implemented two five-day training for women entrepreneurship in Struga and Kicevo micro-region with participation of 46 women.

	Center for Development of the Polog Planning Region 
•	Completed the public procurement process and signed contract with the economic operator ESA Tetovo for delivery of two trainings for start-ups; 
•	Two trainings with 10 start-up delivered; 
•	Public procurement process completed and contract signed with Advantage DOO Skopje for designing marketing solutions for promotion of touristic potentials of the region.

	Centre for Development of Skopje Planning Region 
•	Developed draft versions of the Study for identification and establishment of industrial production clusters, the Regional tourist offer with an action plan and the Brochure of the Business Centre for Support and Consultative Services for SMEs in SPR and processed for commenting to UNDP; 
•	Printed additional Maps of the industrial zones and Promotional brochure of Skopje Planning Region.

	Center for Development of Southeast Planning Region 
•	Launched the process of sharing the e-newsletter with more than 240 business entities from the regions; 
•	One project proposal for IPA cross-border cooperation with Bulgaria submitted and pass the administrative check and the second project proposal for IPA cross-border cooperation with Greece developed; 
•	Implemented quantitative and qualitative research and prepared draft Regional strategy to bridge the gap between the existing supply by educational institutions and business and community needs; 
•	Prepared final version of the Catalog of Services offered by the business sector and delivered for printing.

	Centre for Development of East Planning Region 
•	Completed public procurement process for purchasing furniture for the Business with Drvodekor Enterier from Stip; 
•	53 participants completed two camps for Innovations and entrepreneurial spirit for youth, students, unemployed and potential entrepreneurial; 
•	Two info-days for SMEs managers implemented on the topics of SMEs’ projects in the frameworks of the programme Horizon 2020 and Managerial skills for SMEs’ growth (87 participants);
•	Developed Facebook page and Linkedin profile for promotion of the activities of the Business Centre.  

	The third mission (topic: Support to development of SMEs) of the Czech experts from Berman Group with the 4 centers for Development of Planning regions (Skopje, Vardar, Polog and East) and the Study trip in the Czech Republic were realized. 

	Signed second Annexes with the 5 CDPR (Polog, Skopje, East, Southeast and Southwest) for extension of the period of implementation of the activities and reallocation of incurred savings.
	The Project Team regularly shares information on implemented project activities for the purpose of monitoring the implementation of the 2015-2020 Program for Sustainable Local Development and Decentralization by the MLSG.
	Vardar Planning Region engaged economic operator (Global Project Consulting, Skopje) for development of the Register of potentials for rural tourism, held 3 consultative meetings with regional stakeholders and developed the first draft of the Register; 

	Northeast Planning Region held two consultative meetings with regional stakeholders and developed the first draft of the Register;

	Southwest Planning Region held 4 consultative meetings with regional stakeholders and is in the process of preparation of the draft Register

	Polog Planning Regions re-initiated the process for public procurement for engaging economic operator for developing Registers of potentials for rural tourism - applicants did not meet set criteria;

	Ongoing preparation for arranging meetings with the municipal representatives for the process of development of the territorial networks in Polog and Southwest Planning Region;

	Submitted technical documentation for local road construction for the municipality of Cashka .

2th quarter:
•	Activity for analysis of the operation web portal www.dajpredlog.mk for its improvement and upgrade.
•	Local Assistant for documentation and administrative procedures in the Municipality of Gostivar resigned and the procedure for hiring new person was initiated;

•	The Project Team assisted the MLSG in formulation of 9 measures of Chapter 6 “Openness at the local level” as part of the Third National Action Plan for Open Government Partnership 2016-2018.
	Center for Development of Pelagonija Planning Region 
•	Two submitted projects did not qualify for funding (CIVICA MOBILITAS - Improving energy efficiency and using renewable energy sources and the Government entitled - Lobbying in the decision-making process relating to regulations for urban planning); 
•	The banner of INDR has been uploaded and sent to UNDP for feedback;
•	Coordinative meeting with the chief promoter of the Republic of Macedonia for Izmir Region, Mr. Alev Sulejman was held to discuss potential companies for cooperation from Republic of Turkey.
•	Meeting with representative from the marketing sector of Turkish Airlines for potential cooperation was held and online application form for sponsorship and cooperation was submitted by the Center.
	Center for Development of Southeast Planning Region 
•	Two project ideas that will be used for preparation of project proposal for EU funds application developed - "Youth, Entrepreneurship and traditional crafts” and “Creation of tourism products in the South-East region”; 
•	Regional strategy to bridge the gap between the existing supply by educational institutions and business and community needs prepared; 
•	Catalog of Services offered by the business sector printed in 750 copies.

	Centre for Development of East Planning Region 
•	Furniture for the Business Centre purchased; 
•	Event for observing the Global Entrepreneurship Week – “Revival of the entrepreneurial spirit in EPR” held, attended by 41 participants; 
•	Third info-day for SMEs managers implemented on the topic Co-financing grants for company start-ups and spin-offs for potential applicants held, attended by 39 participants;
•	Final event for promotion of project results held.  

	Completed final report on the implementation of CTF funded project Improved governance for increased competitiveness of four planning regions (Polog, Skopje, East and Vardar) realized in cooperation with Czech consultant company Berman Group. 
	The Project Team regularly shares information on implemented project activities for the purpose of monitoring the implementation of the 2015-2020 Program for Sustainable Local Development and Decentralization by the MLSG.
	Vardar and Northeast Planning Regions developed final versions of the Registers of potentials for rural tourism which have been processed for final proofreading; 

	Southwest Planning Region is in the process of preparation of the draft Register of potentials for rural tourism;

	Polog Planning Regions held two consultative events with the regional stakeholders and developed the first draft of the Registers of potentials for rural tourism which have been processed for further feedback to the national expert and UNDP;

	Polog and Southwest Planning Region held info-events with representatives of Municipalities in the Region for the process of establishing territorial networks for promotion of rural wealth in the both regions;

	In Polog Planing Region 3 municipalities signed the Decision for establishing the territorial network – IMC for promotion of rural wealth, while in Southwest Planning region 8 municipalities signed the document;

	In collaboration with the United Nations World Tourism Organization and the Ministry of Economy, training on Tourism Satellite Account was held, attended by representatives from the Centers for Regional Development.


