4th quarter:
- The technical documentation for the projects in Municipalities on Bogovinje, Caska, Lipkovo and Debarca was hand over to the municipalities on conference on 18.11.2016
- International conference was held in Bitola, Hotel Epinal on 26 - 27.10.2016 with representatives from the business sector from Izmir Region, Republic of Turkey
- Contract was signed for upgrade of the website of the Center for Developments of the NEPR with web portal for the platform for Regional Rural Action of the NEPR

-Needs assessment produced for an electronic platform for external communication of the MLSG;
- An e-catalogue of municipal services established with at least 10 developed procedures;
-“List for establishing the activities of broader importance and interest for which funds could be allocated for stimulating IMC” produced;
-Website for registration of intermunicipal and international cooperation restarted;
-5 networks for inclusive development of the planning regions (Vardar, North-East, South-West, Polog and Pelagonija) design and implement activities for integrated development;
-2 studies prepared related to Interregional Technology Park in East and Veles Planning Region (conceptualization and pre-feasibility studies);
-Roundtable “Neighbourhood Units – unused potential for strengthening the local communities“ was organised with MLSG and CSOs;
-A policy paper “Capital investments for balanced regional development and inter-municipal cooperation“;
-2 studies prepared related to Interregional Technology Park in East and Veles Planning Region (conceptualization and pre-feasibility studies);
-8 Registers of Potentials for Rural Tourism Development available, one for each planning region;
- A cookbook “The Spirit of the Northeast” produced and promoted.

A process-based needs assessment of the MLSG capacities to establish a contemporary online platform for communication was produced, to enable development of a website for an external communication of the MLSG.  
Municipality of Gostivar launched a new service for its citizens and businesses: an interactive e-catalogue of 17 service procedures with a step by step guide on how to acquire them. It includes a variety of services like obtaining a building permit, taxi and transport licences, managing local taxes, licences for small businesses and artisans, etc.  
Petrovec, Staro Nagoricane, Cucer Sandevo, Suto Orizari, Dojran and Debrca were selected as beneficiaries to receive an official website according to the standards for local transparency developed by the MLSG. 
Knowledge sharing in Intermunicipal cooperation reinforced by the reactivation of the website for e-records of intermunicipal and international cooperation of municipalities at the web site: www.imc.org.mk 
MLSG prioritized the municipal competencies where intermunicipal cooperation should be financially stimulated, and produced the “List for establishing the activities of broader importance and interest for which funds could be allocated for stimulating IMC”.
The policy paper “Capital investments for balanced regional development and inter-municipal cooperation“ identified three new policies to be discussed by the MLSG and its partners;
The potentials of the neighborhood units to contribute to the local government system were discussed at the Roundtable “Neighbourhood Units – unused potential for strengthening the local communities“ co-organized with MLSG and CSOs’;
A conceptualization and pre-feasibility study re establishment of Interregional Technology Park in East and Veles Planning Region (ITP) produced, providing a concept and three scenarios for establishment, to be discussed by the mayors of the two regions and serve for decesionmaking re next steps.
Registers of the Potentials for Rural Tourism (RPRT) were produced for Pelagonija, East, South-East and Skopje planning regions. Municipalities, planning regions, tourist organizations from the public and private sector, as well as civil society associations and all other stakeholders can use them for planning their development activities, linking attractions across the region and nationally and create new tourist products, creation of destinations, development of project documentation, negotiations with donors, etc.
Networks for integrated regional development: Vardar Planning Region prepared technical documentation, implementation of the public procurement procedure for reconstructions in the kindergarten “Boris Trajkovski” in Demir Kapija and developed a Programme of the Network for Inclusive Development for 2017-2020; Polog Planning Region established the Network for Inclusive Rural Development (NIRD), developed NIRD Work Programme 2016 – 2018 and accompanying Action Plan 2016 – 2017; South-West Planning Region promoted Work Programme of the Network for Inclusive Regional Development (NIRD) 2017 – 2019 and an accompanying Action Plan 2017 – 2018; improved the Android GIS application “SW Macedonia attractions” developed by the region in 2016; Pelagonija Planning Region: installed solar panels in the kindergarten in the village of Berovci; kindergarten in village Kravari and sport gym of the primary school “Manchu Matak”, village Krivogashtani; trained 26 representatives of the Integrated Network for Regional Development (INRD) and Local Economic Development (LED) units from several municipalities from the region in project cycle management and strategic planning and lobbying; developed a draft e-Guide for project development and implementation for the needs of the IRDN members; established a subgroup of the network focused on social inclusion and developed a project idea for a Day care Centre for Blind and Visually Impaired People in Pelagonija; Northeast Planning Region organized training “Through competitiveness and innovation to successful farming businesses”, training on organic production principles and certification, prepared technical documentation for adaptation of the buildings and parks for the needs of tourism development in the region;

